<DESCRIPT>  VEGETABLE; RECIPE; SUMMER  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Can't get your kids to eat vegetables? Perhaps you're not trying the right
ones. Consider watermelon. Yes, that big summer fruit is really a vegetable --
cousin to the cucumber and kin to a gourd.;    Here are some facts and tips on
watermelon:  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Food  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  NO MATTER HOW YOU SLICE IT,
WATERMELON IN MANY GUISES
GOES A LONG WAY
TO COOL OFF A SUMMER DAY
MIGHTY MELON  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     (box) Rich in vitamin C and potassium, watermelon has 50 calories per cup
and no fat or cholesterol.;    (box) When choosing a watermelon, some people
thump, some smell, some shake, some feel the rind. But one out of four
consumers rely on plain old luck to choose a ripe watermelon.;    (box) The
most reliable method is turn the melon over. If the underside is yellow and
the rind overall has a healthy sheen, the watermelon is probably ripe.;   
(box) Choose a watermelon that if free from dents, bruises and cuts. The skin
should be even, but several insect bites in the rind or marks left from the
vine won't affect the melon's flavor.;    (box) The watermelon should be heavy
for its size.;    (box) Never cook watermelon; cooking returns it to its
cucumber roots, losing texture and sweetness.;    (box) Don't chop watermelon
too finely or it will disintegrate when mixed with other ingredients.;   
(check) Store whole watermelon between 50 and 60 degrees for no more than two
weeks. Once cut and wrapped, watermelon slices should be kept chilled and
eaten within two days.;    (box) Don't wrap pre-cut slices too tightly, or the
flesh will become mushy.;    (box) Freezing also makes watermelon mushy and
mealy.;    (box) All watermelon stored more than two weeks loses its sugar
content and quality deteriorates.;  SUMMER PITA SANDWICH; 4 thin wedges seeded
watermelon; 1 cup diced cooked chicken; 1 tablespoon chopped cilantro; 2
tablespoons plain yogurt;  1/4 teaspoon garlic salt;  Dash cayenne pepper; 2
whole wheat pita breads, halved;  1/4 cup prepared spreadable herb cheese; 4
large lettuce leaves;   Place sliced watermelon on paper towels to remove
excess liquid. Mix chicken, cilantro, yogurt, garlic salt and cayenne. Spread
inside surface of pita bread halves with herbed cheese and fill each with
about 1/4 cup chicken mixture. Arrange watermelon and lettuce in pita bread.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.;  FRESH WATERMELON SALSA; 2 cups seeded and coarsely
chopped watermelon; 2 tablespoons each chopped onion and water chestnuts; 2 to
4 tablespoons chopped <LOCATION>Anaheim</LOCATION> chilies; 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar;  1/4
teaspoon garlic salt; 1 recipe nachos (see below);  Combine all ingredients;
Refrigerate 1 or more hours. Makes 2 cups serving.;    Tip: Serve with grilled
chicken and nachos.; Nachos: Arrange 4 cups tortilla chips in a single layer
on a 10-inch plate. Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Cheddar or jack cheese and
chili powder. Bake at 400 degrees about 5 minutes or until cheese melts;
rotate dish 1 or 2 times. Spoon Fresh Watermelon Salsa over or serve on the
side.;  WATERMELON SMOOTHIE; 2 cups seeded watermelon chunks; 1 cup cracked
ice;  1/2 cup plain yogurt; 1 to 2 tablespoons sugar;  1/2 teaspoon ground
ginger;  1/8 teaspoon almond extract;  Combine all ingredients in blender
container; blend until smooth. Makes 2 to 3 serving.;  WATERMELON FIRE AND ICE
SALSA; 3 cups seeded and chopped watermelon;  1/2 cup chopped green peppers; 2
tablespoons lime juice; 1 tablespoons each chopped cilantro and green onion; 1
to 2 tablespoons minced jalapeno peppers;  1/2 teaspoon garlic salt;  Combine
all ingredients; mix well. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Makes 3
cups.;    Serving Tips: Serve on sliced oranges or cheese-filled manicotti or
with corn or potato chips. Or, top 1 cup dairy sour cream with 1 cup salsa and
serve with chips.;  WATERMELON SORBET;  1/2 cup each sugar, light corn syrup
and water; 2 tablespoons lemon juice; 2 quarts (9 pounds) seeded watermelon
cubes;   Combine sugar, syrup and water; cook and stir over medium heat until
mixture boils. Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Stir in lemon juice. Cool to
room temperature. Puree watermelon cubes in blender; stir in cooled syrup.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions. Makes 1
pint.;  WATERMELON ONION FRESCO SALAD; 4 cups cubed seedless watermelon;  1/2
cup very thinly sliced and quartered sweet onions; 2 tablespoons chopped fresh
basil;  1/4 cup raspberry and/or blueberry vinegar;  Salt and freshly ground
pepper to taste;  Lettuce leaves;   Toss watermelon, onions and basil until
well-mixed. Pour vinegar over watermelon mixture; toss gently to combine
mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Serve on lettuce. Makes 4 to 6
servings.;  WATERMELON RIND; CHUTNEY; 1 quart peeled, diced watermelon rind; 2
cups water; 1 cup packed brown sugar; 2 cups chopped onion; 4 nectarines,
pitted and chopped; 2 <ORGANIZATION>Granny Smith</ORGANIZATION> apples, cored and chopped; 1 cup currants;
1 cup cider or fruit vinegar;  1/4 cup minced fresh ginger root; 2 tablespoons
mustard seed; 2 to 3 cloves garlic, minced;   Combine rind, water and brown
sugar; bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and
simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until thickened; stir occasionally. Stir frequently
during last half hour of cooking to prevent burning and sticking. Makes about
1 1/2 quarts.;  WATERMELON DAIQUIRI; 2 cups seeded watermelon pulp;  1/4 cup
light rum; 2 tablespoons each lime juice and orange-flavored liqueur; 5 to 6
ice cubes;  Garnish:;  Watermelon on a skewer;  Freeze watermelon cubes in
shallow pan 6 hours or longer. Puree watermelon with rum, lime juice and
liqueur in blender until smooth. Add ice cubes, one at a time, and blend until
smooth. Pour into large, stemmed glass and decorate with garnish and a straw.
Makes 1 drink.  </TEXT>
