<SECTION>  Food  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  WILD AT HEART
ALTHOUGH MOST WILD RICE TODAY IS CULTIVATED, IT
STILL HAS THE NUTTY FLAVOR AND CHEWY TEXTURE
RELISHED FOR CENTURIES  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>   1 cup onion, chopped; 1/4 cup butter or margarine; 1 pound ground beef or
ground turkey; 1/4 teaspoon pepper; 4 cups frozen hash brown potatoes; 2 cups
frozen corn, optional; 3 cups cooked wild rice (1 cup raw); 1 10-ounce can
cream-of-chicken soup; 1 cup sour cream; 2 cups mild Cheddar cheese, divided;
1/3 cup bread crumbs;  Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Saute onion in butter. Add
ground beef or turkey, brown and season with pepper. Sprinkle potatoes in
greased 9-by-13-inch pan. Mix together sauteed onion, meat, corn, wild rice,
soup, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Spread on top of potatoes. Sprinkle
remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and bread crumbs on top. Bake 40 minutes. Makes 8
servings.;   Note: This recipe can be prepared, refrigerated overnight and
cooked the following day.;   One serving: 562 calories, 47 gm. carbohydrate,
27 gm. protein, 30 gm. fat, 624 mg. sodium and 94 mg. cholesterol.; GOURMET
BURGERS; 4 pounds lean ground beef; 3 cups cooked wild rice;  Mix ground beef
and wild rice together well. Form into 22 to 24 patties. Freeze in quantities
to suit your family. Defrost before pan frying or broiling.;   Variations:;  
(box) Seasoned burgers -- Add seasoned salt, minced onion, parsley or other
seasoning before freezing.;   (box) Cheeseburgers -- For a hot and wild
cheeseburger, fry or broil thawed hamburgers, add a slice of hot pepper
cheese, place under broiler until cheese melts.;   One burger: 200 calories, 7
gm. carbohydrate, 17 gm. protein, 12 gm. fat, 48 mg. sodium and 54 mg.
cholesterol.; WILD MUSHROOM SOUP; 1/2 cup uncooked wild rice; 4 cups chicken
stock, divided; 3 tablespoons butter or margarine; 1/2 pound nutty-flavored
mushrooms, sliced (such as chanterelles); 1 tablespoon leeks, finely chopped;
3 tablespoons flour; 1 teaspoon paprika; 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard; 2
tablespoons cognac; 1/4 cup whipping cream;  Salt to taste;  In a large
saucepan, combine wild rice and two cups of the chicken stock, bring to a
boil. Reduce heat, simmer 20 minutes covered.;   Meanwhile, melt butter in
heavy skillet, stir in mushrooms and leeks. Saute until mushroom juices start
to evaporate. Sprinkle with flour, stir until bubbly. Stir in the remaining
two cups chicken stock, paprika and Dijon mustard. Bring to a boil. Simmer one
minute, stirring constantly, set aside.;   When wild rice has cooked 20
minutes, stir mushroom mixture into rice. Cover and simmer 25 minutes (for
paddy-grown rice) or until rice is tender (just a few minutes for
hand-harvested rice).;   Stir in cognac and whipping cream. Makes 4 to 6
servings.;   One serving (without salt): 251 calories, 22 gm. carbohydrate, 12
gm. protein, 12 gm. fat, 1130 mg. sodium and 38 mg. cholesterol.; POPPED WILD
RICE; 1 tablespoon uncooked wild rice;  Peanut oil;  Heat half-inch of peanut
oil in heavy skillet just until it starts to smoke. Add uncooked wild rice
kernels, shake pan. Remove from heat immediately; it pops instantly. Drain on
paper towels.;   Note: Cooks won't get much yield in this popping adventure,
but the nutty-tasting result is good to eat by itself or would make an unusual
topping for a salad or casserole.; NORTHWOODS BUTTERMILK CAKE; 2/3 cup wild
rice; 2 cups boiling water; 1 cup whole wheat flour; 2 cups all-purpose flour;
2 teaspoons baking soda; 1/2 teaspoon salt; 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg; 1 cup butter
or margarine; 1 cup packed brown sugar; 1 teaspoon vanilla; 5 eggs; 1/4 cup
vegetable oil; 1/3 cup applesauce, optional; 1 cup buttermilk or sour milk; 
Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a 9-by-13-inch pan. Rinse
uncooked rice, add to boiling water. Simmer, covered for 1 hour (paddy-grown
rice) or until thoroughly cooked with kernels fully open (about 30 minutes for
hand-harvested rice). You should have about 2 cups of cooked rice. Drain well.
Cool completely.;   In medium bowl stir together flours, baking soda, salt and
nutmeg. In a large mixing bowl beat butter or margarine with electric mixer on
medium speed for 30 seconds. Add brown sugar and vanilla, beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each (batter will look
curdled). Add oil and applesauce, blending well after each. Add dry
ingredients and buttermilk alternately to mixture, blending well. Stir in
cooked wild rice.;   Turn into prepared pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or
until done. Test with toothpick. Do not overbake. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Frost with a sour-cream frosting, or
top each serving with whipped cream or a non-dairy topping. Makes 12 large
servings.; STUFFED <LOCATION>TURKEY BREAST</LOCATION>; 1 turkey breast tenderloin (approximately 1
1/2 pound package); 2 cups frozen spinach, thawed and well-drained; 3 cups
cooked wild rice (1 cup raw); 1/4 cup margarine, softened; 1/4 cup raisins;
1/4 cup almonds, chopped; 1/4 cup onion, chopped; 1 teaspoon grated orange
rind; 1 teaspoon lemon pepper; 1/4 teaspoon thyme; 1 tablespoon sherry,
optional;  Margarine or butter, softened;  Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Pound
the turkey breast tenderloin to flatten. Cut breast in half and butterfly each
piece, slicing horizontally almost through the turkey breast starting at the
curved edge. Open each piece.;   Squeeze remaining moisture from spinach.
Spoon half the spinach inside each butterflied half breast.;   In a large bowl
mix cooked wild rice, margarine, raisins, almonds, onion, orange rind, lemon
pepper, thyme and sherry. Spoon 1/2 cup of wild rice mixture evenly over
spinach layer. Roll turkey breasts, starting at pointed short edge. Secure
with string or toothpicks. Set aside.;   Grease 2 1/2-quart square baking
dish. Spoon remaining wild-rice stuffing into dish. Place turkey rolls over
stuffing. Cover. Bake 45 minutes. Remove cover, brush with margarine and bake
an additional 15 minutes.;   Slice each turkey roll into 6 slices and serve
over stuffing. Makes 6 servings.;   One serving: 406 calories, 32 gm.
carbohydrate, 35 gm. protein, 15 gm. fat, 198 mg. sodium and 64 mg.
cholesterol.; WILD RICE SPINACH SALAD;  Salad:; 10 ounces frozen spinach; 3
cups cooked wild rice (2 cups raw); 1/4 cup onion, chopped; 2 cups cubed
turkey; 4 ounces canned sliced water chestnuts;  Dressing:; 1 packet dry
vegetable soup mix; 12 ounces sour cream; 1 cup mayonnaise; 1 teaspoon salt;
1/2 teaspoon pepper;  Drain spinach and press out excess liquid. Combine
spinach with wild rice, onion, turkey and water chestnuts.;   To make
dressing, combine vegetable soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix desired amount into wild rice mixture. Chill at least 1 hour before
serving. Makes 5 main dish servings.  </TEXT>
