<HEADLINE>  HUNGER RELIEF
THIS RECIPE SAMPLER OFFERS DISHES FROM S.F.
CHEFS JOINING TASTE OF THE NATION BENEFIT
TO COMBAT HUNGER  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  BUTTERCAKE; Zola's;  1 1/4 cup butter;  1 1/2 cup sugar;  4  eggs;  3 cups
flour;  2 teaspoons baking powder;  1/2 teaspoon salt;  2 teaspoons ground
anise;   Grated zest of two lemons;  1 cup milk;  1 tablespoon vanilla
extract;  1/2 vanilla bean, split;   Glaze:;  1/3 cup <LOCATION>Pernod</LOCATION>;  1/3 cup lemon
juice;  1/2 cup sugar;   Cream butter and sugar until light. Add eggs one at a
time. Sift dry ingredients together; add vanilla extract and seeds scraped
from inside vanilla bean to milk. Add dry ingredients to butter-sugar mixture
in three parts, alternating with milk. Pour into buttered and floured bundt
pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into cake
comes out clean. Cool, turn out of pan.;    Whisk together glaze ingredients
and pour or brush over cake.;     <LOCATION>CAPPUCCINO BRULEE</LOCATION>; La Folie;  For brulee
mix:;  2 cups heavy cream;  3 tablespoons espresso coffee;  5 large egg yolks;
 6 tablespoons granulated sugar;  1 1/2 teaspoons coffee extract;   For
meringue mix:;  1 cup granulated sugar;  1 cup water;  4 egg whites;   One
pinch salt;   Cocoa powder;   Bring cream to a boil. Add espresso coffee. Whip
egg yolks and sugar to a ribbon. In a fine stream, beat the cream and coffee
mixture into the yolk and sugar mixture. Add coffee extract. Pour through a
fine strainer into pitcher. Place 12 ramekins in a shallow baking dish. Fill
the ramekins with brulee mix. Surround ramekins with hot water until halfway
up the side of the ramekins. Cover with foil or a cookie sheet. Bake about an
hour at 250 degrees or until brulees are firm at the edge, but still soft in
the center. Do not overbake. Chill completely.;    For meringue mix: Place
sugar with the water in a small copper pan and bring to a boil. As the sugar
cooks, beat the whites until stiff. Check the sugar. When it reaches 248
degrees or the hard-ball stage, it is ready to use (if you don't have a candy
thermometer, let a drop of sugar fall from a spoon into a glass of cold water;
the sugar should form a ball and hold its shape on the bottom of the glass).
With the mixer on medium speed, pour the boiling sugar into the egg whites,
being careful not to let it fall on the edge of the bowl or on the beaters,
add salt. Beat until cool. Transfer the meringue into a pastry bag and pipe a
rosette to cover brulee surface, or pile meringue onto brulee with a spoon and
arrange decoratively. Sprinkle with cocoa powder and brown under broiler.
Makes 12 1/3-cup servings.;     MOROCCAN LAMB TAGINE; <ORGANIZATION>Smith Ranch</ORGANIZATION>;  5 pounds
cubed lamb shoulder;  2  yellow onions, sliced;  1/4 cup sliced garlic;  5
cups chicken or lamb stock;  2 ounces butter;  2 tablespoons olive oil;  2
yellow onions, sliced; 10 garlic cloves, minced;  2 tablespoons paprika;  2
teaspoons turmeric;  2 teaspoons cinnamon;  2 teaspoons grated ginger;  1
teaspoon cayenne;  2 tablespoons ground cumin;  1 pinch cardamom;  1  28-ounce
can tomatoes, drained and roughly chopped;  1  6-ounce can tomato paste;  
Salt and pepper to taste;   Bring lamb, onion, garlic and stock to a boil in a
heavy casserole. Skim scum that forms. Reduce to very low heat until lamb is
tender. Meanwhile, melt butter and olive oil in large skillet. Add onions.
When softened, add garlic, paprika, turmeric, cinnamon, ginger, cayenne, cumin
and cardamom. Cook 2-5 minutes. Add tomatoes and paste. Cook two minutes. Add
lamb. Simmer 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Serve over couscous.
Offer harissa (see below).; HARISSA; 15 ancho chiles (soaked, stemmed,
seeded);  1/3 cup lemon juice;  1/3 cup olive oil; 2 tablespoons paprika; 1
tablespoon cayenne;  Pinch black pepper; 2 teaspoons coriander; 1 tablespoon
cumin;  Salt to taste;   Puree chiles, lemon juice and olive oil. Add rest of
ingredients.;     MONSOON ROAST EGGPLANT; <LOCATION>Monsoon</LOCATION>; 2 1/2 pounds unpeeled
eggplant (preferably long purple Chinese variety); 3 tablespoons dark soy
sauce; 2 1/2 tablespoons sugar; 2 tablespoons vinegar; 2 tablespoons peanut
oil; 1 tablespoon chopped ginger; 1 tablespoon chopped garlic; 1 teaspoon
sesame oil;   Toasted sesame seeds for garnish;   Cut eggplant into french
fry-shaped pieces and fry until golden in hot oil (375-400 degrees). (Do not
put too many pieces at a time in oil.) Drain on paper toweling. Mix soy sauce,
sugar and vinegar in a bowl until sugar dissolves. Heat peanut oil in a wok.
Add ginger and garlic, and stir briefly until fragrant. Add sauce, and cook,
stirring briefly until it boils. Add eggplant and toss until well coated. Turn
off heat and add sesame oil. Turn out onto a plate and serve warm or allow to
cool. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.;    Note: Eggplant may be served on toasted
croutons.;     JAMAICAN CURRIED CHICKEN SALAD; <LOCATION>Miss Pearl</LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION>Jam House</ORGANIZATION>;  
Chicken Mixture:; 2 pounds poached chicken meat (shredded); 2 stalks celery,
finely diced; 1 medium red onion, finely diced; 1 bunch green onions, sliced; 
1/2 cup chopped pecans;  1/2 cup chopped dried mango;   Curry Mix:;  1
tablespoon mustard seed;  1 teaspoon fennel seed;  1 teaspoon anise seed;  1
teaspoon coriander seed;  1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper;  1 large pinch of
saffron;  1/4 teaspoon allspice;  2 jalapenos, finely minced;  2 shallots,
finely minced;  2 tablespoons ginger, finely minced  </TEXT>
