<LEADPARA>  Picnic potato salad; needn't be a land mine  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Food  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  SPUD LIGHT  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  for folks watching fat; and cholesterol; Yogurt and pimientos; instead of mayo
and eggs; keep potato salad a part; of healthy picnic menus; This one goes on
the first card; POTATO SALAD;  Salad:; 6 medium potatoes; 3 hard-cooked egg
whites;  1/2 cup finely chopped sweet pickles;  1/4 cup finely chopped onion; 
1/8 teaspoon pepper;  Dressing:; 1 cup plain low-fat yogurt;  1/4 cup
imitation mayonnaise; 6 tablespoons sweet pickle juice; 1 tablespoon prepared
mustard;  <LOCATION>Paprika</LOCATION>;   Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender (about 45 minutes).
Drain and peel while hot. Stir with fork to break up into very small pieces.
Add chopped egg whites, pickles, onion and pepper. Refrigerate in covered
container until serving time.;    For dressing: Mix ingredients together and
refrigerate. Just before serving, mix dressing with potato mixture. Garnish
with paprika. Leftover salad will become dry and need more dressing before it
is served again. Makes 4 to 6 1-cup servings, each containing 3.9 grams of
fat.;    -- From <PERSON>Sonja L. Connor</PERSON> and; <PERSON>Dr. William E. Connor</PERSON>, authors; of "The
New American Diet"; (<PERSON>Simon</PERSON> and Schuster);  FRENCH POTATO SALAD; 1 1/3 pounds
(4 medium) potatoes; 2 tablespoons olive or vegetable oil; 1 1/2 tablespoons
white wine vinegar; 1 tablespoon water; 1 tablespoon Dijon-style mustard;  1/4
teaspoon black pepper; 1 4-ounce jar sliced pimientos, drained;  1/2 cup
sliced green onions; 3 tablespoons chopped parsley; 1 tablespoon chopped fresh
tarragon or 1 teaspoon dried tarragon;  Salt to taste;   In medium saucepan,
cook potatoes, covered, in 2 inches boiling water just until tender, about 30
to 40 minutes. Drain and cool potatoes.;    In large bowl, whisk oil, vinegar,
water, mustard and pepper. Mix in pimientos, onions, parsley and tarragon. Cut
potatoes into 1-inch chunks; add to bowl. Toss lightly to coat and season with
salt. Makes 4 servings, each containing 208 calories and 7.3 grams fat.; 
POTATO-SALAD <LOCATION>TAHITI</LOCATION> WITH; PIMIENTO DRESSING; 1 1/3 pounds (4 medium) potatoes;
1 pound medium shrimp, peeled, deveined, cooked and cooled; 1 cup green bean
pieces, blanched and cooled; 1 cup cherry tomato halves; 4 green onions,
sliced; 1 4-ounce jar sliced pimientos, undrained; 1 clove garlic;  1/4 cup
lemon juice; 2 tablespoons vegetable oil; 1 tablespoon water; 1 tablespoon
chopped fresh dill or 1 teaspoon dried dill weed; 2 teaspoons Dijon-style
mustard;  Salt and pepper, to taste;   In medium saucepan cook potatoes,
covered, in 2 inches boiling water just until tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Drain
and cool potatoes; cut into 1/4-inch slices. In medium bowl, combine potatoes,
shrimp, beans, tomatoes and onions; set aside.;    In food processor or
blender, puree pimientos and garlic. Add lemon juice, oil, water, dill and
mustard; process to blend thoroughly. Add to potato mixture; toss lightly to
coat. Season with salt and pepper. Makes 4 servings, each containing 339
calories and 8.6 grams of fat.; SOUTHWEST POTATO SALAD; 1 1/3 pounds (4
medium) potatoes; 3 tablespoons lime juice; 3 tablespoons vegetable oil; 3
tablespoons water;  1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin; 1 8 3/4-ounce can whole
kernel corn, drained;  1/2 cup coarsely chopped red pepper; 1 cup coarsely
chopped green pepper;  1/2 cup chopped red onion;  Hot pepper sauce, to taste;
 Salt and pepper, to taste;   In medium saucepan, cook potatoes, covered, in 2
inches boiling water just until tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Drain and cool
potatoes.;    In large bowl, whisk lime juice, oil, water and cumin. Mix in
corn, red and green peppers and onion. Cut potatoes into 3/4-inch cubes; add
to bowl. Toss lightly to coat. Season with pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings, each containing 298 calories and 1.1 grams fat.;  POTATO
SALAD; 4 to 5 russet potatoes;  1/2 cup non-fat yogurt; 3 tablespoons
reduced-calorie mayonnaise; 1 teaspoon tarragon; 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard; 
1/2 teaspoon salt;   <ORGANIZATION>Scrub</ORGANIZATION> potatoes thoroughly. Steam until tender. Meanwhile,
combine remaining ingredients. Set aside. Cut potatoes into chunks (do not
remove skin). Pour sauce over potatoes so they are thoroughly coated. Serve
warm or cold. Makes 6 servings with 105 calories per serving.;    -- From
"Eater's Choice" by; <PERSON>Dr. Ron Goor</PERSON> and <PERSON>Nancy Goor</PERSON>; (<LOCATION>Houghton Mifflin</LOCATION>); PARSLEY
POTATO SALAD; 2 cups diced cooked potatoes;  1/2 tablespoon chopped pimiento; 
1/2 cup diced celery; 1 tablespoon chopped onion; 2 tablespoons chopped
parsley;  1/2 tablespoon cider vinegar; 1 teaspoon dry mustard;  1/2 teaspoon
celery seed;  Freshly ground black pepper;  1/4 cup mayonnaise;  Combine all
ingredients except mayonnaise. Toss lightly and chill. A few hours before
serving time, add mayonnaise and return salad to refrigerator. Serve in
lettuce cups, garnished with small strips of pimiento. Makes 4 servings with
145 calories per serving.;    -- From "American Heart; Association Cookbook";
(<ORGANIZATION>David McKay Co</ORGANIZATION>. Inc., <DATE>1984</DATE>); SALADA DE <LOCATION>PALMITO</LOCATION>; E BATATAS; (Brazilian Palm
Heart; and Potato Salad); 2 medium potatoes; 2 cups hearts of palm, thinly
sliced; 2 Spanish black olives, rinsed, pitted and chopped; 1 hard-cooked egg,
chopped;  1/4 cup fresh or frozen green peas, cooked; 1 onion, diced; 1
tablespoon fresh dill, chopped; 2 tablespoons reduced-calorie mayonnaise; 1
tablespoon lemon juice, more to taste;  Garnish:;  Fresh dill, chopped; 2
olives, rinsed, pitted and sliced;  Cook the potatoes in their jackets in
lightly salted water. Peel and dice. Place in a bowl. Gently mix in the next 6
ingredients. Stir together the mayonnaise and lemon juice in a cup. Toss into
the salad. Chill the salad in the refrigerator overnight. When ready to serve,
divide into 4 portions on plates. Garnish with the dill and olive slices.
Makes 4 servings with 74 calories per serving.;    -- From Diabetic Cooking;
from Around the World by; <PERSON>Vilma Liacouras Chantiles</PERSON>; (<ORGANIZATION>Harper &amp; Row</ORGANIZATION>,
<ORGANIZATION>Publishers</ORGANIZATION>,; <DATE>1986</DATE>)  </TEXT>
